Ad Text:
Who We Are

 

iSelect and Compare the Market are trusted, well-known brands dedicated to helping millions of Australians compare and buy personal finance and household products such as insurance, energy, and loans. Together, we provide a seamless, customer-focused experience that makes it easier for Australians to find the right products to suit their needs.

 

What You’ll Be Doing 

Design and implement data pipelines to extract, transform, and load (ETL) data from ERP (e.g., SAP, Oracle, Dynamics, Technology One), HRIS (e.g., Workday, UKG), payroll systems (e.g., Employment Hero, MicrOpay, Payroll Metrics), and enterprise automation platforms.
Develop and maintain data integrations with external financial systems including banking platforms (e.g., payment gateways, direct debit services, reconciliation tools) and taxation systems (e.g., ATO, GST reporting, Single Touch Payroll, PAYG).
Build and manage data flows from recruitment platforms such as LinkedIn, SEEK, and other talent acquisition systems.
Collaborate with business stakeholders to understand data requirements and deliver actionable insights through dashboards, reports, and analytics.
Ensure data quality, integrity, and compliance across all integrated systems.
Monitor and optimize data workflows for performance and reliability.
Maintain comprehensive documentation for data architecture, mappings, and technical specifications.
Work closely with cloud and architecture teams to deploy and manage data solutions in Databricks and Power BI.

What’s In It For You

 

At Compare the Market and iSelect, we’re all about helping people make smart choices – and joining us might just be yours.  We offer an environment where your ideas are heard, your contributions are valued, and your growth genuinely matters. Collaboration is part of our DNA, and you’ll be joining a supportive, forward-thinking team where you can do meaningful work (and be recognised for it!) 

 

We’re guided by three shared values that shape how we work, how we treat each other, and how we show up for our customers - Drive, Noble Intent and All Together.

 

Plus, we offer a range of great perks to help you thrive both in and out of work:

Vibrant and social community who have annual celebrations, family fun days and regular events
Enjoy flexible work arrangements, including the option of one day working from home each week or a 9-day fortnight
Enjoy additional leave days - ‘ME’ leave and ‘Volunteer Day’ leave
Option to purchase additional leave
Return To Work bonus for returning parents
Quarterly Award and Recognition program 

What Sets You Apart 

Strong experience in data engineering and analytics, including ETL processes and data modelling.
Proven track record working with ERP, HR, payroll, finance, and recruitment data.
Familiarity with banking data structures, payment processing, and financial reconciliation.
Experience with taxation data and compliance reporting (e.g., Single Touch Payroll, BAS, PAYG).
Hands-on experience with payroll data and understanding of regulatory requirements.
Proficiency in SQL and programming languages such as Python, R, or Scala.
Experience with AWS data services including Glue and EventBridge.
Experience with data platforms like Snowflake or Databricks.
Understanding of secure data handling protocols and privacy standards.
Strong analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills.

 

At Compare the Market and iSelect we’re proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and we embrace diversity.  

 

This role is available to candidates with unlimited Australian working rights only. Sponsorship is not available.  

 

Compare the Market and iSelect are committed to protecting your privacy. All applications and personal information are kept confidential and securely stored in line with Australian privacy laws, used only for recruitment purposes, and not shared with third parties outside the Auto and General Holdings Group without your consent.

Company Description

About SEEK

SEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities. We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.

Life at SEEK

SEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do. Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Places to Work in Technology (2021-2024). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.

Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting.

Job Description

The Role 

We’re looking for a Lead Data Scientist to lead a high-performing team building end-to-end, data-driven products that create tangible value for hirers and job seekers. In this role, you’ll guide the inference components of our AI/ML products that help SEEK understand the marketplace, and you’ll deliver insightful analysis to enable impactful decision-making across the business. You’ll develop the team’s technical capability and support their career growth while overseeing delivery and partnering closely with Product, Engineering, Strategy, and Commercial stakeholders. 

You’ll thrive in a collaborative, fast-moving environment where alignment, estimation, dependency management, and cross-functional communication are critical. You enjoy being hands-on with models and methods, and you value continuous learning—both for yourself and for your team. 

On any given day, you might assess and guide the development of statistically sound, pragmatic models; prototype and evaluate new approaches to address real business questions; articulate the value created and the risks involved; and refine strategic thinking in partnership with Product Managers, Strategy, Architecture, and Commercial teams. You may collaborate with a dedicated Experimentation team to design and interpret A/B tests, mentor and support other data scientists by validating the value, accuracy, and limitations of their outputs, and work with Engineering and Product specialists to build end-to-end AI/ML solutions. 

Your closest collaborators will include peers across the Data Science stream, stream leads who bring Data Science, Engineering, and Product perspectives to joint problem-solving, and squad leads who track how your team contributes across SEEK’s broader AI initiatives. 

Key Responsibilities 

You will develop a deep understanding of a niche business domain—such as pricing, market position, or ad performance—and the data available to SEEK, translating that understanding into stronger decision-making within your area of responsibility. You’ll help the team turn real business problems into actionable requirements, clearly framing the value and limitations of data-driven approaches and ensuring modelling work is grounded in its business context. 

As a people leader, you’ll coach and sponsor your team’s growth, set clear goals, plan across sprints, define OKRs, and contribute to roadmaps. You’ll champion appropriate ML methods, explaining benefits and trade-offs to audiences ranging from data scientists to colleagues in Engineering and Product, tailoring the level of detail to each stakeholder. You’ll also bring strong delivery management—balancing experimentation with reliability and scale. 

 

Qualifications

You have extensive (8+ years) commercial experience building and improving data-driven products, with deep, hands-on knowledge of machine learning algorithms and model performance tuning. 

You have acted as a conduit between Data Science and Product, Architecture, and Engineering, solving commercial problems. 

You have managed a small team of Data Scientists or delivered large and complex projects. 

You’re highly proficient with Python, SQL, and Spark for data extraction and processing, and comfortable working within modern software development environments and tooling such as Git, AWS, Databricks, and MLflow (or equivalents). 

You communicate clearly, influence effectively across functions, and operate confidently amid ambiguity. 

You’re fluent on the command line in a *nix environment and hold a postgraduate qualification in a quantitative discipline (for example, Physics, Mathematics, Bioinformatics, Computer Science, or Engineering). 

Additional Information

Permanent Perks
At SEEK we offer:

Annual Performance Bonus Plan
Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.
Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave
Support for parents with 14 weeks paid primary carers leave and 2 weeks paid leave for partners

At SEEK, we are passionate about fostering a culture of inclusion and wellbeing that embraces and values the diversity of our people. We are a purpose driven business that works with heart.

We know teams with diverse ideas, experiences and perspectives are more creative and are critical to ensuring effective delivery and innovating to enable our future success. As such, we welcome applications from people with diverse backgrounds and life experiences, especially as they relate to gender, sexual identity, culture, faith, disability and life stages. If you have the skills, curiosity and an adaptable mindset but don't meet every responsibility or qualification listed in this advertisement, please still get in touch with us.

Should you require any specific support or adjustments throughout the recruitment process and beyond, please advise us and we will be happy to assist.

For this role, only those candidates with the eligible right to work will be considered.

SEEK kindly requests no unsolicited resumes or approaches from recruitment agencies and will not be responsible for any associated fees.

Overview

Developers are working hard to build our new reality, and the Azure Experience & Ecosystems Engineering team is here to help. Microsoft Learn offers learning paths, content, and interactive experiences that help people develop the skills that in-demand jobs require. As such, we contribute directly to Microsoft's mission to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more.   As a Software Engineer in Azure Experience & Ecosystems Engineering team, you will build the Microsoft Learn product which will positively impact how people experience Microsoft's technology. You will be responsible for building Content and Learning experiences through constant innovation, design, and implementing state-of-the-art systems. This opportunity will allow you to learn from unique engineering challenges in AI, frontend and backend services and leverage AI to shape Microsoft Learn into a trusted, personalized knowledge platform that meets developers where they are. Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others, and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.

Responsibilities

Works with product management, design and data analyst teams to determine user requirements for a feature.

Supports identification of dependencies, and the development of design documents for a product feature with oversight.

With guidance, learns to create and implement code for a product, service, or feature reusing code as applicable.

Assists and learns about breaking down work items into tasks and provides estimation.

Acts as a Designated Responsible Individual (DRI) in monitoring system/product feature/service for degradation, downtime, or interruptions for simple problems, and recommends actions to restore system/product/service by following the playbook.

Reviews current developments and proactively seeks new knowledge that will improve the availability, reliability, efficiency, observability, and performance of products while also driving consistency in monitoring and operations at scale.

Qualifications

Required Qualifications:

Bachelor's Degree in Degree in Computer Science, or related technical discipline with proven experience coding in languages including, but not limited to, C, C++, C#, Java, JavaScript, or Python - OR equivalent experience.

1+ years of professional experience in cloud service development using one or more of these technologies: Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP), Hypertext Markup Language (HTML), JavaScript, Cascading Style Sheets (CSS), .NET, Node.js, Representational State Transfer Application Programming Interfaces (REST APIs).

1+ year(s) of demonstrated problem-solving, design, and debugging skills, with a passion for quality, performance, and engineering excellence.

Other Requirements:

 Ability to meet Microsoft, customer and/or government security screening requirements are required for this role.

These requirements include, but are not limited to the following specialized security screenings: 

Microsoft Cloud Background Check: This position will be required to pass the Microsoft Cloud Background Check upon hire/transfer and every two years thereafter.    

Preferred Qualifications:

Experience with cloud-native architecture, microservices, and asynchronous workflows. 

Proficiency with agent-based systems, workflow engines, or declarative programming models is highly desirable.

Demonstrated ability with AI-assisted coding tools (e.g., GitHub Copilot) and large language models (LLMs) such as GPT or Claude Sonnet. Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer.

All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances.  We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. If you need assistance and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application or the recruiting process, please send a request via the Accommodation request form.   Benefits/perks listed below may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Microsoft and the country where you work.   #azurecorejobs

This position will be open for a minimum of 5 days, with applications accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled.

Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, citizenship, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, immigration status, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran or military status, race, ethnicity, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable local laws, regulations and ordinances. If you need assistance with religious accommodations and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application process, read more about requesting accommodations.

Ad Text:
Machine-Learning development and operations (MLOps) opportunity
Permanent role in a hybrid work environment - 50% Office/Home
Shape and guide the development of Machine Learning Operations at the Reserve Bank of Australia


We have an exciting newly created opportunity for a Machine Learning Engineer to join our Analytical Centre of Excellence team, where you'll play a key role in delivering scalable, production-ready AI and advanced analytics solutions across the Bank.

As a Machine Learning Engineer, you'll ensure data science applications are robust, maintainable, and aligned with our enterprise architecture, data, and technology standards.

You'll be part of our Data Delivery, Knowledge Management team who are a passionate, collaborative group of problem-solvers who share ideas openly to deliver modern, efficient analytical outcomes for the Bank.

About the role


Collaborate with teams across the organisation to translate advanced data analytics and AI solutions from ideation and requirements gathering to production.
Embed robust Machine Learning Operations practices and capabilities within Knowledge Management to enable scalable deployment, monitoring and continuous improvement of data products and AI systems around the Bank.
Deploy advanced analytical tools, applications, and models into production environments.
Implement solutions to ensure deployed models are observable and explainable
Monitor and maintain production systems, ensuring high availability, performance, and timely updates or retraining.
Manage code versioning, CI/CD pipelines, automation processes, and documentation to support reliable and repeatable deployments and operations.


About you


Demonstrated knowledge of MLOps principles, including CI/CD for ML, dataset and model monitoring, versioning, and lifecycle management.
Demonstrated experience deploying and managing advanced analytical pipelines and models in enterprise environments.
Demonstrated knowledge of scalable system design and integration with enterprise data platforms.
Proficiency in Python, R, and SQL
Demonstrated experience with Microsoft Azure and containerisation technologies (e.g. Docker, Kubernetes).
Demonstrated problem-solving and debugging skills, with a focus on automation and reliability.
Demonstrated ability to collaborate across technical and non-technical teams to deliver business-aligned solutions.
Demonstrated commitment to maintaining high-quality documentation and adherence to applicable information and data management standards.
Familiarity with monitoring and observability approaches and technologies.
Awareness of Data Management & Governance principals.


Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.


Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people. Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go. Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts. We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

Ad Text:
Job description:



EUC Engineer - Intune & Autopilot Specialist

● Design, deploy and manage modern endpoint solutions using Microsoft Intune and Autopilot

● Ensure secure, reliable, and efficient device lifecycle management across the organisation

● Full-time, fixed term (6 months) position

● Based in Macquarie Park, with hybrid work opportunities available

Want to improve the lives of Australians, no matter who they are?

Join us and build a career and future you'll be proud of.

It matters more at Hearing Australia

Hearing Australia is a trusted leader in our field. Working across the country, we exist to support and empower people through hearing health when and where they need it.

Your opportunity

As an EUC Engineer - Intune & Autopilot Specialist, you'll be reporting to the Service Delivery Manager. Your role will focus on the migration from SCCM to Intune and Autopilot, modern device management and deployment, ensuring seamless onboarding and compliance for end-user devices.

Key Responsibilities

Administer Microsoft Configuration Manager (SCCM), Microsoft Intune and Windows Autopilot
Design and implement Windows Autopilot deployment profiles for zero-touch provisioning
Manage application packaging and deployment via Intune
Lead migration from SCCM to Intune for device and application management
Configure and maintain compliance policies, configuration profiles, and conditional access
Administer Azure AD / Entra ID, including identity governance and dynamic groups
Implement security baselines and ensure devices meet compliance standards
Collaborate on Disaster Recovery planning for endpoint technologies
Optimise device lifecycle processes and identify cost-saving opportunities
Maintain accurate documentation and provide training to IT teams


What you'll bring

We believe the successful candidate will demonstrate exceptionally strong customer service values. You'll bring:
Strong experience with Microsoft Endpoint Manager (Intune) and Windows Autopilot
Knowledge of SCCM, Azure AD, and Windows 10/11 deployment
Familiarity with PowerShell scripting for automation
Excellent understanding of security best practices for endpoint management
Ability to troubleshoot and resolve complex device management issues
Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills

Let's create the gold standard of hearing care

We will require the successful candidate to be willing to have a Police Check conducted (we pay), a current driver's licence and must have rights to work in Australia.

Hearing Australia is an Equal Opportunity Employer and embraces diversity, equity and inclusion. We are passionate about building a diverse and inclusive culture from within.

We encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and applicants from different cultures who are bilingual to apply.

We are committed to facilitating a barrier-free recruitment process and work environment. If you require any accommodations, we welcome you to let us know so we can work with you to participate fully in our recruitment experience.

Design it. Build it. Touch it. Join ASA and shape the future of Australian manufacturing with robotics.

Automated Solutions Australia (ASA) is seeking a Mechanical Engineer to develop robotic automation solutions across industries including manufacturing, aerospace, defence, and supply chain.

About ASA:

Why do we do what we do? Simple, to bring world class flexible automation to Australian businesses, allowing them to compete on the global market. We’re proud to invest in local innovation and talent, and we’re committed to reshaping the future of homegrown manufacturing. Joining ASA means stepping into a culture built on trust, respect, and shared purpose, where you’ll work alongside colleagues who push boundaries, support each other, and thrive on teamwork.

At ASA, we’re proud to work with FANUC robots, the gold standard in industrial automation worldwide and it’s exciting to bring that level of technology into Australian businesses right from our Melbourne office. But what really makes the difference is how we use it; our team takes that technology and adds creativity, care, and dedication to design solutions that help our customers upscale and grow. Every project starts with listening to what matters most to them, and our goal is always clear, build automation that’s practical, robust, and effective, while creating partnerships that last well beyond delivery.

The Role:

As a Mechanical Engineer at ASA, you’ll be hands on from concept through to delivery, you’ll be involved in every stage of the project designing, building, and support assembly and installations as needed.

Your responsibilities will include:

Developing concepts and mechanical designs, including 3D models, FEA analysis, and detailed drawings

Creating robot cell simulations and optimising layouts for efficiency and safety

Interfacing machinery with robotic systems to deliver seamless automation

Collaborating with the install team to plan and execute installations

Conducting functional safety assessments and risk analyses

Preparing clear documentation to support each stage of delivery

This is a role where you’ll not only apply your technical skills but also grow alongside a team that values creativity, collaboration, and customer impact.

About you:

You’re the kind of engineer who wants to see your ideas come to life beyond the screen and into real world solutions. Most days you’ll be deep in SolidWorks, modelling, problem solving, and refining designs, with opportunities to support assembly or installations and watch your work come to life. That mix of design and real world impact excites you, because you know the satisfaction comes from building something that works.

You’re detail oriented, a clear communicator, and thrive on learning new things. You know your way around CAD, pneumatics, hydraulics, and servo systems. Experience with robotic automation, in any application, from pick and place to welding, materials handling, or beyond, will be highly valued. But more than ticking boxes, you share our values: creativity, collaboration, and a focus on customer success.

With clients located across Australia, interstate travel may be required. You’ll embrace the opportunity to work closely with them, knowing every project is a chance to strengthen local manufacturing and build partnerships that last.

Applicant Requirements:

Bachelor’s Degree in Mechanical Engineering, Mechatronics or Robotics

An Australian Citizen 

A resident of Australia 

Australian Drivers license 

If this sounds like you, please apply by providing a CV and Cover letter addressed to the General Manager. Step into a role where your ideas don’t just stay on paper, they move, build, and transform the future of Australian manufacturing, with you at the centre of it all.

About us

Boeing Defence Australia is shaping the future of aerospace and delivering some of the nation's most important programs for the Australian Defence Force.

Joining us is a chance to make your mark, working with a diverse team that is united in pushing the boundaries of imagination and excellence.

We currently employ more than 3,000 people across 14 sites in Australia and three international locations and have a range of opportunities available as we plan for future growth.

The opportunity

We are seeking a talented and experienced Detection Engineer to join our growing team. We are seeking a specialist who can establish Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) technologies, onboarding processes for monitoring systems, application monitoring, and developing detection use cases. The ideal candidate will have extensive experience with Splunk, firewall technologies, Threat management tools, and an exposure to incident response. The candidate must have or be able to gain and maintain and NV1 or higher AGSVA security clearance.

Responsibilities:

· Lead the design, implementation, and configuration of SIEM solutions tailored to Boeing Australia's organisational needs.

· Develop monitoring plans in collaboration with system SMEs and onboard monitoring into the SIEM environment.

· Conduct regular reviews and updates of firewall rules and policies to align with security best practices. Utilise threat management tools such as MISP to collect, analyse, and share threat intelligence effectively. Integrate threat intelligence into the SIEM environment to enhance detection and response capabilities.

· Incident response, including detection, containment, eradication, and recovery from security incidents. Contribute to post-incident analysis to identify root causes and recommend improvements to prevent future incidents.

· Prepare and present reports on security metrics, detections, incidents, and trends to management.

· Work closely with cross-functional teams to enhance overall security awareness and practices.

· Provide training and mentorship to junior security staff on SIEM technologies, onboarding processes, detection use cases, and incident response procedures.

Experience/Qualifications

· NV1, NV2 or the ability to hold and maintain NV1.

· Minimum of 5 years of experience in information security, with a focus on SIEM technologies, particularly Splunk.

· A diploma or degree in cyber security, IT, related discipline or equivalent experience

· Strong experience in onboarding systems and applications into SIEM environments.

· Familiarity with application monitoring best practices and tools.

· Proven experience in creating detection use cases based on threat intelligence and threat assessments.

· Experience with firewalls and network security principles.

· Familiarity with threat management tools, specifically MISP, and their application in security operations.

· Proven experience in incident response, including the ability to manage and mitigate security incidents effectively.

· Relevant certifications related to Splunk, or incident handling are a plus.

· Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, demonstrating attention to detail.

· Strong communication skills, both verbal and written, with the ability to convey complex security concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Preferred Skills:

· Experience with scripting languages (e.g., Python, PowerShell) for automation and integration tasks.

· Knowledge of compliance frameworks (e.g., ISM, DSPF, NIST) and their application in security practices.

· Familiarity with cloud security principles and technologies.

Applicants must be Australian Citizens to meet Defence security requirements.

Culture

We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workplace. Female applicants, people of Aboriginal or Torres Strait Island descent and ex-defence personnel are encouraged to apply.

Benefits

· Flexible working options

· Study assistance

· Salary packaging

· Employee Incentive Program

· Global opportunities

How to apply

If you are ready to join an innovative industry leader, click Apply Now.

Making a difference isn’t just our purpose, it’s what motivates our people every day. For us, work is not about ticking a box. It’s about knowing that it matters. We make a meaningful difference every day by making it easier for our customers to focus on what matters in their lives.

Here’s how you will make a difference in this role…

McMillan Shakespeare is accelerating its digital transformation, and we’re looking for a Power Platform Engineer to help build modern, scalable solutions across Power Apps, Power Automate, Power Pages and Dynamics 365.




Power Platform Engineer designing, building, and supporting enterprise Power Apps, Automate, Pages, and D365 solutions to drive digital transformation.




You’ll design, develop, and support enterprise-level applications that directly improve customer experience and business productivity.

At MMS clear expectations help our people Be the Difference.  Your key responsibilities in this role will include:




Build and enhance Power Apps, Power Automate flows, Power Pages and Dataverse solutions.

Customise and extend D365 Sales & Service (plugins, workflows, JavaScript).

Integrate with Azure services (Logic Apps, Functions, APIs).

Troubleshoot incidents, manage deployments, and support CI/CD pipelines.

Work with Product Owners, BAs, Developers and Architects in an Agile environment.

Ensure secure coding, governance, and best-practice Power Platform standards.

To be considered for this role you will possess the following:

Strong hands-on Power Platform experience.

Experience with D365 customisation and .NET plugin development.

Skills across JavaScript, TypeScript, C#, .NET, REST APIs, and Azure.

Understanding of ALM, CI/CD, Git and DevOps practices.

Clear communication, ownership, and the ability to deliver in a fast-paced environment.

Degree in IT/Computer Science (or equivalent experience). Microsoft certifications a bonus.

Why join us

Work on enterprise-scale digital projects.

Hybrid working and supportive team culture.

Opportunities for certification and growth.

Impactful role in a major ASX-listed organisation.







What we can offer you:

Novated leasing benefits and discounts

12 weeks paid parental leave and access to our Parents Portal

Comprehensive learning and development opportunities to support your career growth

Sonder digital wellbeing platform, providing personalised support 24/7, plus annual flu vaccinations

Default Income Protection Insurance reimbursed for members of the MMS Default Super Fund

HorizonOne are excited to be partnering with Icon Water to recruit new team members into their Digital Technology Group. 

Wholly owned by the ACT Government, Icon Water has delivered essential services to Canberra for over 100 years. While primarily a water and sewerage provider, it also invests in electricity and gas through private partnerships, operating across both government and commercial sectors. Icon Water is focused on sustainability, playing a key role in addressing climate change, protecting the environment, and achieving net zero emissions by 2045.
 
Serving approximately 190,000 customers, the business manages over $3.2 billion in assets—including dams, treatment plants, reservoirs, and networks of mains and pumps—and generates around $490 million in annual revenue.
 
The Opportunity

Icon Water is progressing through a significant digital and data transformation, making this a highly impactful time to join. In this permanent, ongoing role, you will help build on the foundation for the organisation’s self-service analytics capability an area with high business engagement and demand.

This is a great permanent opportunity for a data analytics engineer to join a small, growing team where you will directly influence data capability, architecture decisions, and the future direction of the function.

Help define the direction of data-driven decision-making and uplift the organisation’s use of data
Strong demand from business teams for better data insights. You’ll be stepping into a role where your work is immediately valued and needed.
Work on genuinely interesting data problems, connecting information from multiple sources to uncover insights.
Exciting pipeline of interesting data projects to influence and be part of
Please view the candidate information page for this role here: bit.ly/H1DTGrecruitment   
 
The Role

Key responsibilities include:

Collect and clarify reporting and dashboard requirements, identify data sources, and secure required access from data owners
Extract, integrate, clean and transform data from SQL, on-prem, API and cloud systems using Power Query (M), ADF, SSIS and dataflows to build reusable semantic models
Apply dimensional modelling (star/Kimball) and optimise models for refresh, performance and organisation-wide reuse while minimising duplication
Automate data extraction at source by developing SQL/OData queries and Power Automate flows, reducing manual processes and shifting transformations upstream
Maintain and enhance existing dataflows and semantic models, ensuring alignment with business needs and managing endorsement, permissions and governance
Support business users through training, walkthroughs and documentation, and develop reports where Power BI capability is limited
The Ideal Person

You bring your intermediate or above skills in Power BI (in particular DAX, data flows and semantic models) and are comfortable working with SQL and cloud-based data environments.

You take a thoughtful approach to data, ensuring models and reports are accurate, reliable, and fit for purpose, and you can translate what a business asks for into what they truly need in a clear and approachable way. You take a methodical approach to your work an understand the importance of careful documentation, and data governance.

You’re positive, curious and are looking for a long term role that you can grow, develop within as you continue to deepen your knowledge of the organisation, data and people so you can help others get the most from their data.
 
Salary / Rate

The salary band starts at $121,253 + 15% Super.
 
In addition to an attractive renumeration package, Icon Water offer great employee benefits including flexible working arrangements, career development opportunities, health and wellbeing contributions and salary sacrifice options to name a few. 
 
How to Apply

To apply online, please click on the appropriate link.
 
Alternatively, for a confidential discussion, please contact Lucas Walker on 02 6108 4878 quoting ref no. 21160

Applications close Sunday 7th December at 11:59pm (AEDT). Early applications are encouraged, as we will review them as they are received.
 
HorizonOne is committed to building a diverse and inclusive workforce and we encourage applications from people of all cultures, capabilities and backgrounds.

Job Title: Data Migration & Fabric Data Warehouse – Multiple Roles
Ad Text:
IM Systems (IMS) is a strategic innovation consultancy specialising in aligning technology, data, and people to unlock real business potential. 

We partner with many of Australia’s most recognised public and private organisations, providing both strategic direction and hands-on expertise across digital, data and AI initiatives. 

At IMS, we value individuality, encourage innovation, and invest deeply in our people. We offer flexible work arrangements and foster a culture built on excellence, curiosity, and collaboration. 

Our consultants bring expertise across a broad range of domains including Data Governance, Data Strategy, Enterprise & Solution Architecture, Document & Records Management, Master Data, Business Intelligence, Analytics, Data Migration, Data Warehousing, AI/ML, Big Data and Program Management. 

Current Opportunities – Multiple Roles (6+ Month Contracts & Permanent) 

We are expanding our pool of highly skilled data professionals. Over the coming months, we will be onboarding talent across several data migration and data warehouse projects. Engagement durations vary from 6 to 12 months, with some permanent roles available. 

We are seeking experienced professionals for the following: 

Program Management – experience running both large scale data migration engagements, and data warehouse implementation engagements. Working with a sizeable team plus multiple parties to achieve high quality outcomes on time and on budget. Experience with ERP and/or health systems an advantage. 

Data & Solution Architecture & Analysts – data practitioners experienced in one or more of the following: data modelling (Erwin); data mappings; data architecture; solution architecture; data security; metadata management; encryption. 

Data Engineering – data engineers with experience in one or more of the following: MS Fabric / Databricks; batch / near real-time / CDC; CI/CD pipelines.  

Data Analytics & BI – practitioners to define, design and build out dashboards and/ or web applications. Skill sets needed include technical / data analysts; Power BI; AI / ML; Copilot. 

Data Governance – experience with data catalogues for glossaries, data lineage, data quality; establishing and populating templates (automated scanning). Experience in one or more of the following Purview; Informatica IDMC; Quest DI.

What We’re Looking For 

3+ years’ experience through to 10+ years as seasoned practitioners or leaders 

Eligibility to work in Australia 

Hybrid working model: 2–5 days per week onsite in Melbourne CBD 

Relevant qualifications and certifications valued 

Strong communication skills—both written and verbal 

High attention to detail and commitment to quality 

Ability to translate business needs into clear technical and functional documentation 

Collaborative approach, with the ability to work effectively across business, data and technical teams 

If you’re a confident, client-focused professional who thrives both independently and within team environments, we’d love to review your resume.  

Prior applicants are welcome to reapply. 


No agencies please.
